            <li ><h3 class="H1">Place Name :</h3> Nazare, Portugal</li>
            <li><h3 class="H1">Description:</h3>One of the most famous and largest waves in the world is based in Nazare, Portugal. The fishing community is in the Oeste area of Portugal, in the Leiria District, in the ancient Estremadura province . Despite being famous among all the other surfing places around the world for decades, the spot didn’t earn widespread notice until 2011. Garrett McNamara rode a massive wave in Nazare in 2011, earning the title of “biggest wave ever ridden” in the Guinness Book of World Records. He smashed his own benchmark there in 2013, and Rodrigo Koxa won the title in 2017 by surfing an 80-foot wave there.</li>
           
            <li><h3 class="H1">Best Time to Visit:</h3> October- March</li>
