</li>
            <li><h3 class="H1">Description:</h3>Cloudbreak, located off the coast of Tavarua Island in Fiji, is one of the world’s most famous reef breaks. Known for its powerful, long, and perfectly barreling waves, Cloudbreak offers a challenging and exhilarating surf experience. The wave breaks over a shallow coral reef and can reach heights of up to 20 feet on big days, making it a magnet for advanced surfers seeking the ride of a lifetime.</li>
            <li><h3 class="H1">Things to Do:</h3>What sets Cloudbreak apart is not just the wave but the idyllic setting. Surrounded by crystal-clear waters, palm-fringed islands, and luxury resorts, Fiji offers the ultimate tropical surf experience. After a day of challenging waves, surfers can relax in paradise, enjoying the island’s laid-back vibe, stunning sunsets, and warm hospitality. Whether you’re paddling out to Cloudbreak or exploring the surrounding reefs, Fiji offers a surf adventure like no other.</li>
            <li><h3 class="H1">Best Time to Visit:</h3>The best time to surf Cloudbreak is during the Fijian winter (May to October), when the Southern Hemisphere swells create the ideal conditions for this world-class wave. While Cloudbreak can be intimidating, nearby breaks like Restaurants and Namotu Lefts offer more forgiving waves for intermediate surfers.</li>
